        <b><span id="titleLabel">3.2 - Reaching the connected consumer: Tapping their personal networks and power of persuasion</span></b>
        <table border="1" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <tr>
                <td class="tableCell" colspan="2"><span id="dateTimeLabel">Wednesday, May 10, 11:30 AM - 1:00 PM</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="tableCell" colspan="2"><span id="roomLabel">Room 408B</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="tableCell" colspan="2"><span id="descriptionLabel">Fully immersed in their iPod, PSP, or 3G handsets, today's consumers are busy, actively sharing music and photos, streaming satellite radio, and communicating with friends via IM and blogs. They are too skeptical to be swayed by traditional print ads, 30-second spots, or marketing calls. Instead, pro blogs, programmed word of mouth campaigns, and strategically deployed armies of covert product ambassadors are among a marketer's secret weapons. This session will explore the influence factors that guide the purchasing decisions of today's youth market. Whose information do they trust? Which brands do they believe in? How important is price? How do they communicate with their network of friends? Knowing how consumers think and what they are motivated by can help you map out an effective sales strategy. Hear from marketing experts and researchers how your game can maximize its presence among connected consumers. Instead of going against their style, make their passion, opinion, and power of persuasion work for you.</span></td>
            </tr>
